    <p>After-hours, when GPs aren't available, expats can call the medical on-call service (continuità assistenziale or turno medico), which provides coverage for urgent but non-emergency medical needs. These services offer telephone consultations and can arrange house visits if necessary. For minor urgent care needs like sprains, minor lacerations, or non-emergency infections, urgentology centers (centri di urgenza) provide faster service than emergency rooms without the costs of emergency transport.</p>

