    <p>If traveling internationally from Italy, obtain a medication list in Italian from your doctor listing medication names, dosages, and frequencies. Italian healthcare professionals recognize generic medication names better than brand names, making this documentation useful for refills or medical consultations abroad. Expats with chronic conditions should register with Italian healthcare providers before traveling extensively, ensuring prescriptions can be refilled locally if needed. Some medications available by prescription in home countries are available over-the-counter in Italy, potentially saving money and pharmacy visits.</p>

