    <p>Oral rehydration salts are crucial for treating diarrhea and dehydration—these are available in Italian pharmacies (sali reidratanti) but having a supply from home is convenient. Probiotics may help prevent traveler's diarrhea and are readily available in Italian parafarmacie. Preventing gastrointestinal issues involves basic hygiene like handwashing, eating cooked foods at appropriate temperatures, and drinking bottled water in uncertain situations. Most Italy travelers experience no GI issues, particularly those eating at established restaurants in major cities.</p>

