    <p>Cough and cold medications for children are available with age-appropriate formulations. Expectorants help clear congestion, while cough suppressants reduce troublesome coughing. Italian pharmacies provide suspensions suitable for infants and young children who can't swallow tablets. Antihistamines for allergies are available in pediatric strengths, addressing seasonal or environmental allergies affecting children. Anti-nausea medications, intestinal flora restoration products (probiotics), and constipation treatments serve various pediatric needs. Always verify age-appropriateness before administering medications to children.</p>

