    <p>Upper respiratory infections (colds) are common in children and typically resolve with supportive care, rest, and hydration. Over-the-counter remedies like saline nasal drops help clear congestion without medication. Humidifiers ease respiratory symptoms, particularly during nighttime sleep. Fever management using appropriate medications keeps children comfortable while their immune systems fight infections. Most childhood colds resolve within a week, and antibiotics are unnecessary unless secondary bacterial infections develop.</p>
