<p>Cost represents a primary consideration differentiating daily and monthly contact lenses. Daily disposable lenses cost approximately €25-40 per box of 30 (representing one month supply for one eye). For both eyes wearing daily lenses, monthly cost ranges €50-80; yearly cost totals approximately €600-960. This higher cost reflects: manufacturing expense of 365 individual lenses annually per eye, premium quality standards, and convenience. Monthly lenses cost approximately €10-20 per box in Italian pharmacies (representing 30-day supply for one eye). For both eyes, monthly cost is €20-40 per month; yearly cost totals approximately €240-480. This significantly lower cost reflects: manufacturing fewer lenses, simpler solution chemistry, and less packaging per lens. Monthly solutions cost additional €5-15 monthly, totaling approximately €60-180 yearly, bringing combined monthly lens + solution cost to €300-660 annually for both eyes. For budget-conscious expats, monthly lenses represent substantially lower ongoing expenses. For convenience-prioritizing individuals, daily lenses cost differential (€300-600 yearly per person) may represent acceptable investment. Families with multiple contact lens wearers see costs multiply substantially, potentially motivating switch to monthly lenses or combination of contacts and glasses.</p>

