<p>The Calendario Vaccinale begins at birth with hepatitis B vaccination, protecting against hepatitis B virus infection. At 2 months of age, infants receive a comprehensive vaccination package including hexavalent vaccine (protection against diphtheria, tetanus, pertussis, polio, hepatitis B, and Haemophilus influenzae type b), pneumococcal vaccine (PCV13), and rotavirus vaccine. At 4 months, infants receive second doses of hexavalent, pneumococcal, and rotavirus vaccines. At 6 months, third doses of hexavalent and pneumococcal vaccines are administered, plus additional hepatitis B protection if needed. This intensive early immunization period provides essential protection when infants are most vulnerable to serious infectious diseases. These combination vaccines (like hexavalent) reduce the number of injections needed, making the vaccination schedule feasible and well-tolerated. Your pediatrician (pediatra) in Italy schedules these appointments and explains vaccination benefits and any side effects. Parents receive vaccination cards (libretto vaccinale) documenting each vaccination, which serve as official records in Italy and internationally.</p>

