<p>Hepatitis A vaccine protection likely lasts 20-30 years or longer after the complete two-dose series. Hepatitis B vaccine protection lasts decades or potentially lifetime after the complete series. Studies ongoing in vaccinated cohorts suggest protection is sustained years after vaccination, making booster vaccination unnecessary for most individuals.</p>

