<p>Italian dermatologists manage a wide range of skin conditions including acne, rosacea, eczema, psoriasis, fungal infections, warts, moles, skin cancer screening, and cosmetic dermatology. Dermatologists can prescribe topical treatments (creams, lotions, ointments), systemic medications (oral pills or injections), and perform procedures like laser therapy, chemical peels, and minor surgery. Understanding which conditions your dermatologist specializes in helps ensure you're seeing the right specialist.</p>
