<p>When over-the-counter topical antifungals fail to clear infection after 4 weeks of consistent use, dermatologists may prescribe stronger topical or oral antifungal medications. Prescription-strength azole creams (higher concentration than OTC versions) provide more potent treatment. Oral antifungal medications including fluconazole, itraconazole, and terbinafine tablets are prescribed for infections unresponsive to topical treatment or for infections in areas difficult to treat topically (like nail fungus or scalp ringworm).</p>
