<p>Ringworm (tinea corporis) appears as itchy, red, ring-shaped patches on skin. Despite the name, ringworm is a fungal infection, not a worm. It's contagious through direct contact or contaminated surfaces. Mild ringworm responds to topical antifungal creams applied twice daily for 2-4 weeks. However, ringworm tends to recur; treating for the full recommended duration even after symptoms resolve is important to prevent relapse.</p>
